<br>
1) Some form of self speedup is always handy, and necessary for most targets.  Sow Potions, jboots, or travellers boots will supply this function nicely.<br>
2) pull 4 likely victims with your trusty staff of the temperate flux (or some other quick, low damage spell, or just run up to them and take some lumps).  I heavily recommend the staff, as it can be used to judge range while running away as well as making an excellent pulling tool.  It is instant cast, which means it cannot be interrupted and so you can use it's effect while running.<br>
3) find a big area where you won't agro more mobs.  Run in wide circles until mobs are closely grouped (the round up).  Before casting your snare, make sure you have a long straight stretch to use (the runway).<br>
4) to cast a spell on pulls like this, I would always stop and turn about 5-10 degrees.  If you don't turn, or turn too much (say 45-135 degrees) your casting will probably be interrupted.  Turning fully around (180 degrees) seems to work pretty well also.  This turn is needed to let the server know that you've stopped moving.<br>
5) use an AE snare such as bonds of force or atol's spectral shackles to snare them (get to extreme range before attempting this to avoid getting yourself or getting hit/stunned by your victims).  I use Atol's spectral shackles because of the extra duration (2:30 instead of 2:00) and the extra slowdown.<br>
6) use a good AE spell (circle of force at 34, or the Pillar series at 51+) to nuke all four at once.<br>
7) Find a quiet place to med up, and read the paper, or a book, or chat with all your friends.<br>
<br>
A few notes/dangers:<br>
1) if one or more of the mobs resists snare, it is a pain because by the time you get the distance to snare the one that resisted, you will lose the others if they are giants, and otherwise they will just be a long ways away.  Getting them rounded back up (and then resnared -- important!) can be challenging.<br>
2) Judging the radius of the round up circle can be tricky.  The times I've come close to dying have usually been at this stage.  Note that if the grouping isn't tight enough after the snare, you may have to circle them another time or two before doing damage spells.<br>
3) This does not work with casting mobs.  This is because casters will stop to cast on you at different times.  This will get them out of sync and break up the group.<br>
4) Mobs which usually run at low health will not run as long as there are 2 or more mobs still up and chasing you.  This actually makes quad kiting easier as they stay grouped rather than splitting with one running and the other chasing.  However, it does make it difficult to use Harvest to get that last bit of mana to finish off large mobs.  I will sometimes use a draught to finish off one if 2 almost dead mobs are still on my tail.<br>
5) Sometimes people see a wizard with 4 giants on his tail and think he is in distress.  They will &quot;help&quot; by pulling off one or two of your carefully orchestrated pull.  This is annoying, but they mean the best... after they see you consitently pulling 3-4 at once and then coming back 2 minutes later to med next to them they'll get the idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
6) It is possible to group with people doing this, but it takes a bit more skill.  Having a druid to pull of the one that resisted your initial snare can be a big help.  And any nuking character can help finish them off -- just be careful not to nuke too early or they will split agro and wreck the whole AE spell thing.<br>
7) Your connection quality has a direct impact on your ability to quad safely.  I found that a ping time (the number on the left side of the meter) of 250 was the highest I could have and still be fairly safe.<br>
<br>
Most of all, this is a lot of fun to do.  Yes you med a lot between your pulling sessions, but the pull itself is quite challenging and just dangerous enough to keep it exciting.  I have done hundreds of quad pulls (probably closer to a thousand) when I haven't had the time (or timing) to get a group, and haven't died yet (though I've come close a few times).<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>
